b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Frase and Rytr share a solid foundation of core features including Long Form, Short Form, Seo Tools, Templates. Where Frase pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Team Collaboration, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Rytr uniquely offers Tone Control and Plagiarism Check and Multilingual and Browser Extension, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Frase holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Rytr scores 6/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Rytr comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Frase begins at $15/mo. Rytr stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Frase requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
